article.headline: Grambling St. 87, Prairie View A&M 73
article.story: GRAMBLING, La. (AP) -- Andre' Ratliff scored 28 points on 9-of-13 shooting while Anthony Williams recorded his fifth double-double of the season with 17 rebounds and 14 points to help Grambling defeat Prairie View A&M 87-73 on Saturday night. Andrew Prestley and junior Kendric Baker scored 13 each for Grambling (10-9, 8-4 SWAC), which led 42-34 at halftime. Prairie View (5-18, 3-8) was led by Brian Ezeh with 28 points, while Andy Genao scored 13 and Derek Johnson 10. The Panthers got as close as 49-41 with 15:06 to go, but the Tigers responded with a 13-4 run to push their lead up to 62-45 and Grambling cruised from there.
